-- Morocco's Saham Group Says it Expands Into The African Insurance Market
-- B y   A i d a   A l a m i
-- 2010-11-22T16:46:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-22/morocco-s-saham-group-says-it-expands-into-the-african-insurance-market.html
Morocco’s Saham Group has bought a
92-percent controlling stake in the insurance company Colina,
the private holding group said in a press release.  Casablanca-based Saham, founded in 1995, engages in the
franchising of children’s clothing stores. Colina has 15
affiliates in 11 African countries including Senegal, Mali and
Cameroun, Saham said in the press release. The deal will be
finalized in the coming weeks, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aida Alami in Cairo at 
 aalami2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
